c="false" toc-caption="PART 2 PERSONAL INJURY DAMAGES [ss 9&#x2013;26]"><leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.PT2.D7"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="division" searchtype="LEGISLATION DIVISION" subdoc="false" toc-caption="DIVISION 7 STRUCTURED SETTLEMENT [ss 22&#x2013;26]">
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="DIV-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.PT2.D7" type="ext"/>DIVISION 7</designum></desig><title searchtype="DIV-TITLE">STRUCTURED SETTLEMENT [ss 22&#x2013;26]</title><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[Div 7  insrt Act 92 of 2002  sÂ 3 and Sch 2, effective 10 January 2002]</text></p></leg:histnote></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S22"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[270,495] s 22 What is a structured settlement">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S22" type="ext"/>[270,495]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">What is a structured settlement</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>22</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>For the purposes of this Division, a <defterm><emph typestyle="bf">structured settlement</emph></defterm> is an agreement that provides for the payment of all or part of an award of damages in the form of periodic payments funded by an annuity or other agreed means.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[270,500] s 23 Court required to inform parties of proposed award">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23" type="ext"/>[270,500]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Court required to inform parties of proposed award</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>23</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The purpose of this section is to enable the court to give the parties to proceedings a reasonable opportunity to negotiate a structured settlement.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A court that decides to make an award of personal injury damages in respect of future loss (not including interest) exceeding $100,000 must first notify all the parties to the proceedings of the terms of the award it proposes to make.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>In addition, if the court considers that the person may be a person in need of protection, the court is to notify the Protective Commissioner under the NSW Trustee and Guardian of the terms of the award it proposes to make.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (3)  am Act 49 of 2009  Sch 2.8[1], effective 1 July 2009]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.4" type="ext"/>(4)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The notification must set out the amount of each component part of the proposed award in accordance with the requirements of the regulations and rules of court.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.5"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.5" type="ext"/>(5)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>In this section:</text></p>
<deflist><defitem id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.PERSON-IN-NEED-OF-PROTECTION"><defterm><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S23.PERSON-IN-NEED-OF-PROTECTION" type="ext"/><emph typestyle="bf">person in need of protection</emph></defterm> <defdesc>
<p><text>means a person who is liable to be subject to an order that the estate of the person be subject to management under the NSW Trustee and Guardian Act 2009 because the person is not capable of managing his or her own affairs.</text></p>
</defdesc></defitem></deflist><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (5)  am Act 49 of 2009  Sch 2.8[2], effective 1 July 2009]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S24"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[270,505] s 24 Court may make consent order for structured settlement">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S24" type="ext"/>[270,505]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Court may make consent order for structured settlement</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>24</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A court may, on the application of the parties to a claim for personal injury damages, make an order approving of or in the terms of a structured settlement even though the payment of damages is not in the form of a lump sum award of damages.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S25"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[270,510] s 25 Obligation of legal practitioners to provide advice">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S25" type="ext"/>[270,510]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Obligation of legal practitioners to provide advice</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>25</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An Australian legal practitioner must advise, in writing, a plaintiff who proposes to negotiate a settlement of a claim for personal injury damages about the following:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S25..A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S25..A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>the availability of structured settlements,</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S25..B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S25..B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>the desirability of the plaintiff obtaining independent financial advice about structured settlements and lump sum settlements of the claim.</text></p>
</li>
</l><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[s 25  am Act 98 of 2005 s 3 and Sch 3.8, effective 24 November 2005]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S26"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[270,515] s 26 Offer of structured settlement &#x2014; legal costs">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S26" type="ext"/>[270,515]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Offer of structured settlement &#x2014; legal costs</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>26</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S26.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S26.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.LPAN04.S340" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Section 340</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Legal Profession Act 2004 extends to an offer of compromise by way of a structured settlement on a claim for personal injury damages.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (1)  am Act 98 of 2005 s 3 and Sch 3.8, effective 24 November 2005]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S26.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S26.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>In that case, the court is to have regard to the cost to the defendant of the proposed structured settlement as compared to the lump sum payment of damages when determining whether a reasonable offer of compromise has been made.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level></leg:levelbody></leg:level-vrnt></leg:level></leg:body></LEGDOC>